---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Google Ads Management — Meridian Digital" description="Home services businesses use Meridian to generate more leads via Google Ads. Campaign management, daily optimization, transparent reporting. Book a free strategy call.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[85vh] flex items-center bg-gradient-to-b from-dark to-dark-card">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 pt-32 pb-20">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent mb-6">Google Ads Management</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold text-hero-text leading-[1.05] tracking-tight max-w-4xl">
        Your ads are running.<br />
        <span class="text-accent">Are they working?</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-body-muted max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        Most home services businesses either burn through ad spend with nothing to show for it, or they turn off Google Ads entirely because it "didn't work." It works. The management is the difference. I set up campaigns correctly, optimize them daily, and give you a clear picture of what's actually producing calls and jobs.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-accent hover:bg-accent-hover text-white font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Book a free strategy call
        </a>
        <a href="#how-it-works" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-4 border border-dark-border text-body-muted hover:text-white hover:border-white/20 font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          See how it works
        </a>
      </div>
      <!-- Social proof -->
      <div class="mt-16 flex items-center gap-6">
        <div class="flex -space-x-3">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent/20 border-2 border-dark flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-medium text-accent">AC</div>
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent/30 border-2 border-dark flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-medium text-accent">PJ</div>
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent/40 border-2 border-dark flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-medium text-accent">+</div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-body-muted">Working with HVAC, plumbing, roofing, and electrical shops across the US.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who this is for -->
  <section class="bg-white py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight">Who this is for.</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text-light-text text-lg leading-relaxed">
            This is for home services businesses — HVAC, plumbing, electrical, roofing, contractors — that are spending money on Google Ads or thinking about it, and want someone who actually understands the platform to run it.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-8 space-y-4">
            <li class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/10 text-accent text-sm font-bold">1</span>
              <span class="text-light-text"><strong class="text-dark">You're spending $3K+/month</strong> on Google Ads and not sure if it's working or just burning</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/10 text-accent text-sm font-bold">2</span>
              <span class="text-light-text"><strong class="text-dark">You need steady inbound calls</strong> — not volume, but actual jobs booked from people who found you on Google</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/10 text-accent text-sm font-bold">3</span>
              <span class="text-light-text"><strong class="text-dark">You're the decision-maker</strong> — no committee, no approval chain, just you deciding what makes sense for the business</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/10 text-accent text-sm font-bold">4</span>
              <span class="text-light-text"><strong class="text-dark">You want transparency</strong> — to know what's working, what's not, and why we're making the changes we're making</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-dark rounded-2xl p-8 border border-dark-border">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-hero-text mb-6">What most businesses experience before working with us</h3>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5">&#10007;</span>
              <p class="text-body-muted text-sm">High ad spend, low lead volume. Campaigns are broad match and burning through budget on junk clicks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5">&#10007;</span>
              <p class="text-body-muted text-sm">Agency or in-house person who sets it up and then barely touches it until the monthly call.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5">&#10007;</span>
              <p class="text-body-muted text-sm">Reports that show impressions and clicks but not which calls actually turned into jobs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5">&#10007;</span>
              <p class="text-body-muted text-sm">No visibility into what's happening between report cycles. Problems compound for weeks before anyone notices.</p>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-dark-border my-6" />
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-hero-text text-sm font-medium">After working with us: campaigns optimized daily, leads tracked to source, cost-per-call measured against actual revenue.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section id="how-it-works" class="bg-hero-text py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight">How it works</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-light-text text-lg">Setup done right. Optimization done daily. Reporting done honestly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-16">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <span class="text-sm font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Week 1</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark mt-2 mb-4">Campaign Audit & Setup</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">
              If you have existing campaigns, I audit everything — account structure, keywords, negative lists, ad copy, bidding strategy, conversion tracking. If you're starting fresh, we build from scratch with the right foundation: service-specific campaigns, tight keyword targeting, and call tracking from day one.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2 text-light-text">
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Full account audit (if existing campaigns)</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Conversion tracking setup — calls, form submits, both</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Call tracking numbers per campaign</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Keyword research specific to your service area</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Ad copy written for your business</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-dark">Account audit report</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-dark">Conversion tracking verified</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8h2a2 2 0 012 2v6a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2v4l-4-4H9a1.994 1.994 0 01-1.414-.586m0 0L11 14h4a2 2 0 002-2V6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2v4l.586-.586z" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-dark">Keyword strategy document</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M11 5H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v11a2 2 0 002 2h11a2 2 0 002-2v-5m-1.414-9.414a2 2 0 112.828 2.828L11.828 15H9v-2.828l8.586-8.586z" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-medium text-dark">Campaigns live and running</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div class="md:order-2">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Every Weekday</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark mt-2 mb-4">Daily Optimization</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">
              Campaigns aren't "set and forget." Every business day I review what's happening — which ads are getting clicks, which keywords are burning budget with no conversions, which service areas are performing and which are bleeding money. I make adjustments in real time, not at the end of the month when the damage is done.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2 text-light-text">
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Bid adjustments by service area and time of day</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Negative keyword mining — blocking wasted clicks daily</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Ad copy testing and rotation</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Budget reallocation toward what's working</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Quality Score and ad rank monitoring</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="md:order-1 bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-light-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Monday</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-dark">Budget review — reallocate from underperforming campaigns to top performers</p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-4">
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-light-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Midweek</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-dark">Negative keyword mining — block new irrelevant search terms eating budget</p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-4">
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-light-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Friday</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-dark">Weekly performance summary — leads, cost, cost-per-call, what's next</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <span class="text-sm font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Every Month</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark mt-2 mb-4">Honest Reporting</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">
              No vanity metrics. You get a monthly report that connects ad spend to actual business outcomes — calls logged, jobs booked, revenue attributed. If something isn't working, I tell you why and what I'm going to do about it. No spinning a bad month into a win.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2 text-light-text">
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Total calls, form submits, and cost per lead by campaign</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Ad spend vs. prior month — with explanation of any variance</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Month-over-month trend analysis</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> What's working, what's not, and the plan for next month</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> 30-minute strategy call each month</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
            <div class="text-center mb-6">
              <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-accent" id="placeholder-metric">—</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-light-text">Average cost-per-lead reduction (typical client, 90 days)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
                <span class="text-light-text">Calls tracked</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-dark">Logged daily</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
                <span class="text-light-text">Ad spend reconciliation</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-dark">Monthly</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
                <span class="text-light-text">Strategy calls</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-dark">30 min/mo</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between text-sm">
                <span class="text-light-text">Campaign adjustments</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-dark">Every business day</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="bg-white py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight">Straightforward pricing.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-light-text text-lg">Management fee + your ad spend. No hidden fees. No percentage of ad spend games.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Starter -->
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-dark">Starter</h3>
          <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-accent mt-2">$500<span class="text-lg font-normal text-light-text">/mo</span></p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-light-text text-sm">For businesses spending up to $5K/month on Google Ads.</p>
          <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Campaign setup (up to 3 campaigns)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Up to 100 tracked keywords</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Daily bid optimization</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Weekly performance summary</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Monthly strategy call</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Conversion tracking setup</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Call tracking (up to 3 numbers)</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Growth -->
        <div class="relative border-2 border-accent rounded-2xl p-8">
          <span class="absolute -top-3 left-8 bg-accent text-white text-xs font-medium px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Most Popular</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-dark">Growth</h3>
          <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-accent mt-2">$750<span class="text-lg font-normal text-light-text">/mo</span></p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-light-text text-sm">For businesses spending $5K–$15K/month on Google Ads.</p>
          <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Everything in Starter</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Up to 6 campaigns (service + location splits)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Up to 300 tracked keywords</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Ad copy testing and rotation</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Bi-weekly strategy calls</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Call tracking (up to 8 numbers)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Competitor spend monitoring</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scale -->
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-dark">Scale</h3>
          <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-accent mt-2">Custom<span class="text-lg font-normal text-light-text">/mo</span></p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-light-text text-sm">For businesses spending $15K+/month or with complex multi-location needs.</p>
          <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Everything in Growth</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Unlimited campaigns and keywords</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Multi-location management</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Weekly dedicated strategy calls</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Custom reporting dashboard</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
              <span class="text-accent font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-dark text-sm">Priority turnaround on adjustments</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center mt-12 text-light-text">
        Not sure which tier fits? <a href="/contact" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-medium transition-colors">Let's talk.</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="bg-dark py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-hero-text leading-tight mb-12">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-10">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-hero-text mb-2">What's the minimum ad spend to work together?</h3>
          <p class="text-body-muted leading-relaxed">I recommend at least $3K/month in ad spend for it to be worth running Google Ads effectively. If you're spending less than that, you're better off with SEO or a more targeted local strategy. If you're spending more than that, we can talk about whether the account is structured right.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-hero-text mb-2">How is this different from the agency I'm already using?</h3>
          <p class="text-body-muted leading-relaxed">Most agencies manage hundreds of accounts and touch yours once a week at best — usually less. I work with a limited number of clients at a time, which means your account gets attention every business day, not just when the monthly report is due. You'll also talk to me directly, not an account manager who barely knows your account.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-hero-text mb-2">Do you charge a percentage of ad spend?</h3>
          <p class="text-body-muted leading-relaxed">No. I charge a flat management fee. Your ad spend goes directly to Google — I don't take a cut of it. This keeps incentives aligned: I want your campaigns to work efficiently, not just generate spend.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-hero-text mb-2">What if I don't know how much I'm spending on ads?</h3>
          <p class="text-body-muted leading-relaxed">We start with an audit of your current account — I'll tell you what you're spending, where it's going, and whether it's working. That audit is included. If you don't have campaigns running yet, we build from scratch with the right foundation.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-hero-text mb-2">How do you track if calls are turning into jobs?</h3>
          <p class="text-body-muted leading-relaxed">We set up call tracking — you'll have dedicated numbers per campaign so you know exactly which ad generated each call. Whether those calls turn into jobs is your side to track, but I'll give you the data to connect the dots. If you use a CRM or booking system, we can integrate that too.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-hero-text mb-2">Is there a contract?</h3>
